@node "which_network" " Which Network card?    "

 Interfacing to PC ISA network card:

 EmuNet uses standard packet driver commands on your network card.
 It does not require special functions to be provided by the packet
 driver. However as of current implementation your packet driver
 should report CL_ETHERNET (ethernet class) otherwise emunetd.exe
 will refuse to work with it.
@endnode

@node "bugs_limitations" " Bugs/Limitations          "

  There are bound to be bugs in a program of this kind, and I'd be grateful
  if you would send detailed reports for any bugs you do find. 

  As ever, be  careful about backing up your data! and do not rely
  on the network transfer of important data without ever testing
  it for a longer period.

  Here is a listing of bugs/limitations that I could detect so far:

 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Bugs/Limitations

  * If EmuNet does not function with the packet driver supplied 
    with your network card , you may try to use the alternative
    packet driver collection by crynwyr. See the pcbin/HOWTOGET.IT
    file for further info.

  * I implemented the Goldengate Support using the knowledge from my
    other project (AmiCDEx). However, I cannot test this feature for
    real and if you get any problems using this with your board please
    provide as much info as you can (a@{" debug " link "debug" 0}output would also be fine).
@endnode

